_"Finesse The Plug" _ (phrase, informal) - Smooth talking your way into getting more dope for less…
Clandestine record label, The Trilogy Tapes, tear up the NTS studios once a month, ripping through the grittiest and muddiest tracks. No words on this one, just tunes.
Artist Peter J Doyle & friends enter the uncanny valley of their music collections, traversing folk, soul, psychedelia and much more…

Desire paths are formed by repeated deviation from official routes.
Artist/producer Laura Groves explores private roads and dreamscapes with a series of mixtapes featuring demos, synth sketches, collaborations, pop classics, field recordings and soundtracks.
"Raga Vibrations" is a monthly selection of Indian music curated by Greg Davis.

nts1.n: THE ONE GLOVE BREAKFAST SHOW W/ MACCA
nts1.d: Stay left and take a trip with Macca's Saturday breakfast show on NTS. Weekend musings and eclectic cuts from all over the place, it's a low-key affair and you're all invited. ONE GLOVE!!!

Eglo Records' main man Alexander Nut joins us for some slick late night futurism. Broken beat, soul, and whatever else happens to take his fancy.
From the host: "A live recording of Alex Nut b2b Mr Scruff, taken from last Sundays final Eglo Records session at Corsica Studios, ahead of the club closing in March. Corsica Studios has been the labels late night London home for the last 10 years, so we had to have a proper send. The recording is a 2 hour segments of what was an special 6 hour back to back set from label boss Alex Nut and our good friend Mr Scruff."

Machi, the Paris-based music archivist and content creator who shares the history, places and people behind music from across the world picks out an hour of records, each from a different corner of the globe.

nts2.d:
Luis Alvarado is a record producer, curator, and independent researcher based in Lima, focused on art and sound, and experimental music. He is the director of the record label Buh Records, distinguished for its work in the historical archiving of avant-garde and experimental music from Peru and Latin America. Tune into his monthly residency here.
From the host: "More than a genre, indie was an ethic: recording with whatever was available, releasing independently, and operating outside established circuits. Between 1994 and 2005 in Lima, that mindset reshaped local rock, opening space for noise rock, indie pop, shoegaze, and a garage impulse."

nts2.d: bản mix phù họp cho bạn big boi đi công viên nước có con ròng ba đầu
The revered Japanese noise artist stops by for a regular NTS slot, playing some surprising selections from his diverse & deep record collection.

We have a very special guest mix by the one and only Keanu Nelson. For those not familiar with Keanu’s work, he's an artist based in Papanya, Northern Territory, Australia. His debut album was produced and recorded by Yuta Matsumura, who is behind such groups as The Lewers, Low Life & Orion. Keanu’s warm and very heart yearning lyrics are sung in both his native language and english, this paired with Yuta’s analogue-esqe beats and keys is a real angelic treat. I hope you enjoy some of Keanu’s favourite tracks that inspire him daily and a few of his gems from the debut album.
Irregular extra special shows from the world of Melbourne reissue label Efficient Space.

nts2.n: Recorded Live at Bourse de Commerce w/ Megabasse
nts2.d: In May 2024, Megabasse - the solo project of French musician Pierre Bujeau - unveils at the Bourse de Commerce his litany-like, mysterious, and obsessive compositions, his back turned to the audience and a double guitar slung over his shoulder, where repetitive motifs layer and unfold endlessly, enveloping the space in a reverberating poetry.

nts2.n: TAFELMUSIK W/ FRANCESCO FUSARO - György Kurtág Special
nts2.d:
Francesco Fusaro, the man behind MFZ Records and classical music recording series 19'40'', brings a considered and varied selection of baroque, classical and contemporary music for a full two hours each month.
From the host: "A centenary episode for György Kurtág: from the playful shocks of Játékok to the raw lyric theatre of Kafka-Fragmente, Messages of the Late Miss R.V. Troussova, and Beckett’s Endgame. With Bach chorales as quiet points of reference."

Hannah Catherine Jones splits things open for the Opera Show: an exploration of the best in opera old and new, as well as an unearthing of the operatic in other records from soul, jazz or further afield.
From the host: "An ongoing series reflecting on and celebrating the life of my dad - the late Roy Durban Jones - who taught me and many, many others so much about music, including opera."

subtle.d: Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.
BirdE brings an hour of the freshest Drum and Bass covering everything from liquid to techy steppers - the deeper the better.

Originally from Cambridge, Counter Culture's selection deftly navigates across a myriad of influences and exclusives from himself & friends.
Expect some of the freshest rolling soul straight to your headspace.

What's The Weather, Selecta? w/ Megan Wroe

subtle.d:
Hailing from Mumbai, now living in London, Chaitu is energised by the UK sound and scene.

With a love of all things weird, weighty and groovy; his mixes and productions bridge electro, techno, breaks, UKG and Jungle, with sprinklings of everything in between.

Chaitu champions provocative beats that break down the barriers of style, genre and expectation, all while keeping you moving.

In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.

subtle.n: THE CULTURE HEAD w. SAINT VOX

subtle.d: With a monthly show on Subtle, Niceup is a London based DJ with a unique style. Pushing UKG, Breakbeat, Bass, Electro and 140. Weaving through genres showcasing new releases and older cuts.

Jedah started DJ'ing at the tender age of 18 years of age specialising in UK Garage/Grime. 

Jedah is currently the DJ for Grime Original Hollowman Jendor of the former Grime Collective Essentials/ OG's.

Responsible for “that massive grime tune with the Psycho strings”, UK producers/DJs Trends & Boylan are well versed in what the scene has to offer. They use this platform to showcase music from across the 140 spectrum from Grime to Dubstep. Anything goes!!

XOSÉ is a DJ and aspiring producer mixing and making mostly UK Garage, Grime and UK Funky. FORWARD PRESSURE largely focuses on the aforementioned UK born genres, though you can expect a variety of UK influenced sounds.

Sempra is a producer & DJ based in London, specialising in the fusion of UK Garage, Jungle and Breakbeat with dreamy vocal melodies and the beautiful instrumentation found in Soul and contemporary RnB. Sempra’s consistent output has been released by labels such as Future Classic and Headroom, gaining industry support from the likes of Nia Archives, Sherelle, Yung Singh and Dr Dubplate.

Cicely is a northern raised London based music photographer and DJ. From learning to mix during lockdown, she has since played at clubs across the country in venues such as Fabric, Corsica and Fold.

Cicely runs a collective and events night under the name NRG CRU which focus heavily on the high energy rave sound. She is highly influenced by the northern sound she grew up with, and you can hear this within her sets. Expect heavy blends of techno and hardcore while she shines the light on her favourite northern artists.
